short head
Homonym Number:
Word Class:verb
Sense Number: 1
Definition:[heading dogs] to stop closely on the shoulder of a mob of sheep with inadequate control of the whole mob.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
