Date: 0/0/1927
Source: Sheep-Dog, The
Author: WHYTE
Vol / Page: 44
Edition:
Quote: It is fault for a dog to short-head his sheep i.e. not go sufficiently round, but to stop on the shoulder.
Notes:

Date: 0/0/1964
Source: Practical Guide to Handling Dogs and Stock
Author: MILLS ET AL
Vol / Page: 36
Edition:
Quote: If Boy stops to the right of this line he is said to have 'short-headed' .. From a distance it is often difficult to be sure if a dog has stopped on the point of balance, or overrun his head, or has short-headed .. by shortheading he leaves the other side - the escape side - wide open.
